[{'author_name': 'Gregory Hardin', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116240317398441253380/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiC3jIGQBrDCj7YySmDCu0YS2HVAIkOOvho2yIxGsU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '4 months ago', 'text': "Finding TJ's in New York was a happy surprise after moving from LA. Cashiers can offer excellent conversation at this location. Seriously. Diverse and rich with experiences and intellectual curiosity. Can really turn your day around and as always, easy on your wallet.

reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Gregory Hardin', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116240317398441253380/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiC3jIGQBrDCj7YySmDCu0YS2HVAIkOOvho2yIxGsU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '4 months ago', 'text': "Finding TJ's in New York was a happy surprise after moving from LA. This was my first. Simple layout, everything in front of you. Line can be out of the door though. Usually a busy, after work evening before the weekend. But just go get a slice of pizza next door. Or get a beer around the corner. Have a small slice of life on your shopping trip. Unique ability to do this in New York.
